        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 6:28PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Calico, or 5 miles west of Pine Ridge, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pine Ridge, Calico, and Number 4.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
